   Did you know?...Section 2.05, Title 19, California Code of Regulations
   provides that any person may request a code interpretation from the
   State Fire Marshal. wedge How to Request a Code Interpretation from
   SFM??

   Governor Appoints State Fire Marshal and Assistant State Fire Marshal

   John Tennant - State Fire Marshal

                                     John J. Tennant - State Fire Marshal
                                     See Governor Press Release

   We are pleased to announce the appointment of our State Fire Marshal,
   John J. Tennant!! Governor Gray Davis announced this appointment on
   November 27, 2000. John Tennant is a member of the Pasadena Fire
   Fighters Association, California Professional Firefighters, the
   National Fire Protection Association, and the International Association
   of Fire Fighters. He held the position of Fire Captain with the City of
   Pasadena Fire Department, and has spent more than 28 years working in
   fire suppression and fire prevention.

   Nancy Wolfe - Assistant State Fire Marshal

   Nancy Wolfe - Assistant State Fire Marshal
   See Governor Press Release

   Congratulations to Nancy Wolfe! Governor Gray Davis has appointed Nancy
   Wolfe, as the Assistant State Fire Marshal. This announcement was also
   made on November 27, 2000. Nancy Wolfe was formerly the Chief of Fire
   Prevention. She's been with the State Fire Marshal's office since 1979
   and a manager with this office since 1986. Nancy Wolfe has served as a
   member of the California Fire Chiefs Association and the National
   Association of Pipeline Safety Representatives.
   State Fire Marshal Appoints Chief of Fire Prevention

   Randy D. Roxson - Chief of Fire Prevention

   Randy D. Roxson - Chief of Fire Prevention

   The State Fire Marshal has appointed Randy D. Roxson as Chief of Fire
   Prevention, effective April 6, 2001. Randy Roxson served in the United
   States Air Force from 1975-1979 as a Firefighter/Rescue Crew Member.
   Thereafter, as a Federal Civilian Firefighter for 2-1/2 years with the
   United States Navy. He came to the State Fire Marshal's Office in 1982.
   Chief Roxson's education includes an A.A. in Fire Science (1981), B.A.
   in Political Science (1988), and Juris Doctorate (1994).

   He has been an Attorney at Law since 1996, and is as a member of the
   California State Bar, Sacramento County Bar Association, California
   District Attorneys' Association and the American Bar Association.

